When I became Catholic he gave me Cost of Discipleship by Bonhoeffer four decades ago. The theme in both was a call to arms (action), to be awake, to watch what’s around you and call it out. Francis sent a flare off with who he was standing with on the Vatican balcony. Even his chosen name is camouflage from who he is. I think to be traditional is to be Catholic. Catholic CRT is the rest
